def equalize_img(img, pmin=2, pmax=98):
    img = (img - np.percentile(img, pmin)) / (np.percentile(img, pmax) - np.percentile(img, pmin)) * 255
    img = np.clip(img, 0, 255).astype("uint8")
    return img

メタデータを使って、グローバル※な地形による輝度補正をする¶

Radiometric Calibration of S-1 Level-1 Products Generated by the S-1 IPF

$ \sigma_0 = \frac{DN^2}{A^2_{dn}K}\sin(\alpha) \\ A_\sigma = \sqrt{\frac{A^2_{dn}K}{\sin(\alpha)}} $

$A_\sigma$ sentinel-1 DN

$ \sigma_0 = \frac{DN^2}{A_\sigma} $

# read sentinel-1 metadata
tree = ET.parse(calibration_path)
root = tree.getroot()

azimuthTimes = []
lines = []
pixels = []
sigmaNoughts = []
for calibrationVector in root.iter("calibrationVectorList"):
    for azimuthTime in calibrationVector.iter("azimuthTime"):
        azimuthTimes.append(dateutil.parser.parse(azimuthTime.text))
    for sigmaNought in calibrationVector.iter('sigmaNought'):
        sigmaNoughts.extend([float(x) for x in sigmaNought.text.split(" ")])
    for line, pixel in zip(calibrationVector.iter("line"), calibrationVector.iter("pixel")):
        lines.extend([int(line.text) for _ in range(int(pixel.get("count")))])
        pixels.extend([int(x) for x in pixel.text.split(" ")])
        
Y = np.arange(0, img.shape[0], 1)
X = np.arange(0, img.shape[1], 1)
lines = np.unique(lines)
pixels = np.unique(pixels)

# scipy.interpolate.interp2d 2d grid RectBivariateSpline
f_sigmaNought = interpolate.RectBivariateSpline(lines, pixels, np.array(sigmaNoughts).reshape(len(lines), len(pixels)))
sigmaNought = f_sigmaNought(Y, X)

plt.imshow(sigmaNought)
plt.show()

補正係数を軌道情報から雑に求める¶

$\alpha$ (local incident angle) = $\alpha$

$ A_\sigma = \sqrt{\frac{C}{\sin(\alpha)}} \\ C: constant $

# 

tree = ET.parse(annotation_path)
root = tree.getroot()
sat_positions = []
for positions in root.iter("position"):
    sat_position = []
    for position in positions:
        sat_position.append(float(position.text))
    sat_positions.append(sat_position)

sat_velocities = []
for velocities in root.iter('velocity'):
    sat_velocity = []
    for velocity in velocities:
        sat_velocity.append(float(velocity.text))
    sat_velocities.append(sat_velocity)
    
orbit_timestamps = []
for orbit in root.iter("orbit"):
    for t in orbit.iter('time'):
        orbit_timestamps.append(dateutil.parser.parse(t.text).timestamp())
orbit_timestamp_ref = orbit_timestamps[0]
orbit_timestamps = [orbit_timestamp - orbit_timestamp_ref for orbit_timestamp in orbit_timestamps]

position_spline_funcs = []
for i in range(3):
    position_spline_funcs.append(interpolate.interp1d(orbit_timestamps, np.array(sat_positions)[:,i], kind='cubic'))
    
velocity_spline_funcs = []
for i in range(3):
    velocity_spline_funcs.append(interpolate.interp1d(orbit_timestamps, np.array(sat_velocities)[:,i], kind='cubic'))

# read sentinel-1 metadata
tree = ET.parse(annotation_path)
root = tree.getroot()

lines = []
pixels = []
lats = []
lons = []
azimuth_times = []
for geolocationGrid in root.iter("geolocationGrid"):
    for geolocationGridPoint in geolocationGrid.iter("geolocationGridPoint"):
        for item in geolocationGridPoint.iter("line"):
            lines.append(int(item.text))
        for item in geolocationGridPoint.iter("pixel"):
            pixels.append(int(item.text))
        for item in geolocationGridPoint.iter("azimuthTime"):
            azimuth_times.append(dateutil.parser.parse(item.text).timestamp())
        for item in geolocationGridPoint.iter('latitude'):
            lats.append(float(item.text))
        for item in geolocationGridPoint.iter('longitude'):
            lons.append(float(item.text))

# 

Y = np.arange(0, max(lines), 1)
X = np.arange(0, max(pixels), 1)
lines = np.unique(lines)
pixels = np.unique(pixels)

f_longitude = interpolate.RectBivariateSpline(lines, pixels, np.array(lons).reshape(len(lines), len(pixels)))
f_latitude = interpolate.RectBivariateSpline(lines, pixels, np.array(lats).reshape(len(lines), len(pixels)))
f_azimuth_time = interpolate.RectBivariateSpline(lines, pixels, np.array(azimuth_times).reshape(len(lines), len(pixels)))
lons = f_longitude(Y, X)
lats = f_latitude(Y, X)
azimuth_time_sar = f_azimuth_time(Y, X) - orbit_timestamp_ref

# 
surface_position = np.array(pymap3d.ecef.geodetic2ecef(lats, lons, np.zeros(lats.shape)))
sat_position = np.array([position_spline_func(azimuth_time_sar) for position_spline_func in position_spline_funcs])

# 
norm_vector = np.array(pymap3d.ecef.geodetic2ecef(lats, lons, np.zeros(lats.shape) + 1)) - surface_position
norm_vector /= np.sqrt(np.sum(norm_vector**2, axis=0))
look_vector = surface_position - sat_position
look_vector /= np.sqrt(np.sum(look_vector**2, axis=0))

# 
incident_angle = np.arccos(np.sum(norm_vector * look_vector, axis=0))

# 
coef = np.sqrt(1 / np.sin(incident_angle))
